NZ Stocks Finish Lower
Wellington , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- The New Zealand sharemarket drifted lower in moderate trading on Friday as the record-high close on Wall Street on Thursday had little effect on the local market .
The NZSE40 Index ended eight points lower at 2286 with a turnover of more than 52 million NZ dollars ( 30 million U.S. dollars ) .
The main leaders were mixed .
Among the weaker leading stocks , Air New Zealand eased 3 cents to close at 206 cents while Fletcher Energy and Telecom shed 5 cents each to stand at 625 cents and 820 cents respectively .
Carter Holt Harvey lost 6 cents to reach 261 cents .
The stronger leaders included Brierley Investment , rising 2 cents to 116 cents , Lion Nathan 2 cents to 422 cents and Fletcher Building also 2 cents to 407 cents .
